\ Heavy statistics benchmark: non-parametric bootstrap of a Firth-penalized
\ logistic regression on the synthetic 1M-row dataset, serial vs parallel.
\ Resamples REPS times, fits every resample each way, and times both. The
\ serial==parallel check is a corruption canary for the worker-local collector.
\ Regenerate data/logistic-sim.tsv with bench/gen-logistic-sim.l4 if missing.

"lib/statistics.l4" load

: REPS 50 ;
: WORKERS 6 ;

"data/logistic-sim.tsv" read-tsv 1 rows>dataset to ds
ds [ :x1 :x2 :x3 :x4 :x5 :x6 :x7 :x8 ] dataset>matrix with-intercept to X
ds [ :y ] dataset>matrix to Y
X Y augment to data
data dim drop to n

7 seed
REPS iota [: |> i | data n resample-indices select-rows :] map to resamples

now to t0
resamples ' fit-augmented-logistic map to serial-betas
now to t1
resamples WORKERS 1 ' fit-augmented-logistic pmap-ext to pmap-betas
now to t2

"rows=" . n . "reps=" . REPS . "workers=" . WORKERS . cr
"serial   (s):" . t1 t0 - . cr
"parallel (s):" . t2 t1 - . cr
"speedup     :" . t1 t0 - t2 t1 - / . cr
"match       :" . serial-betas pmap-betas = . cr
